    <briefdescription>
<para>The 3 callbacks that implement a custom animation. Only the <computeroutput>.update</computeroutput> callback is mandatory, <computeroutput>.setup</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>.teardown</computeroutput> are optional. See the documentation with the function pointer typedefs for more information. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>The <computeroutput>.setup</computeroutput> callback is called immediately after scheduling the animation, regardless if there is a delay set for that animation using <ref refid="group___animation_1ga178f894a2045805bca61cee16f6a8eed" kindref="member">animation_set_delay()</ref>.</para>
</simplesect>
The diagram below illustrates the order in which callbacks can be expected to get called over the life cycle of an animation. It also illustrates where the implementation of different animation callbacks are intended to be “living”. <image type="html" name="animations.png" inline="yes"></image>
